[normal]I write on behalf of this association 
[normal]and following a meeting of our supporters on 15
[normal]th
[normal] November 2013.  
[normal]Cornwall
[normal]'s Community Standards Association
[normal] was founded in 1974 to voice concern about declining standards in society, particularly in relation to their effect on children and families.  Supporters meet bi-monthly and those attending our last meeting include a retired secondary school head teacher,
[normal] a minister of religion, retired nursing professionals, parents and a local councillor.  We are of varying ages. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.
[normal]              
[normal]It has always been argued
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]but
[normal] it is
[normal] perverse not to acknowledge
[normal] today
[normal],
[normal] that watching sexual promisc
[normal]uity and indulging in the portrayal of extreme violence contribute to the emergence of a violent society.  Numerous competent research projects have judged this to be so.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.
[normal]              
[normal]It was our view
[normal], expressed in the 1970's and 1980's to the then British Board of 
[normal]Film Censors, that the industry's rather than the public's choice influenced the Board's decision
[normal]s
[normal] and standards.  
[normal]So also with the BBC.
[normal]  Reconsideration of the BBC Trust's role offers an opportunity to consider Lord Reith's original vision and aim to real
[normal]ise it more completely than at present.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.
[normal]              
[normal]The Prime Minister h
[normal]as
[normal] acknowledged that 
[normal]Great Britain
[normal] is a Christian country.  History describes plenty of shortcomings but today international scholars such as Dr 
[normal]Vishal
[normal] 
[normal]Mangalwadi
[normal] in his mammoth research 
[normal]f
[normal]o
[normal]r
[normal] 
[normal]The Book that made your world - How the Bible created the soul of Western civilisation
[normal], challenge
[normal]s
[normal] Western nations to take their spiritual and moral foundations much more seriously as serious signs of decay threaten.
